  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Ethical review boards should oversee clinical and research AI use, ensuring adherence to data privacy and security best practices 42, 50.",
    "Unlike many international ethics bodies, U.S. IRBs exclude societal harms from their review criteria, which may prevent long-term effects from hindering beneficial research.",
    "However, this approach risks overlooking broader implications.",
    "Federal regulations explicitly state that IRBs should not consider the long-range effects of research on public policy, which may inadequately address the ethical and societal risks arising from AI's broader impacts 51.",
    "While entities such as the World Health Organization and the Biden administration have developed criteria for safe, fair, and transparent AI, comprehensive AI governance systems that function enterprise-wide are still lacking in many academic institutions, companies, and startups."
  ],
